page.title: 12HOME LIFE LAURA'S DAY
page.content: Laura Marshall is ten years old and goes to West Grimstead School. She wakes up at six thirty a.m on Saturday mornings.She gets up at seven forty five a.m,dresses,and has muesli and bread or egg and bread.After breakfast she feeds her rabbit Smokey and lets him out of his hutch into his run.she cleans her teeth and brushes her hair.Sometimes she does her piano practice.At eight forty she cycles to choir practice.She comes back at ten twenty.She does many differant things before lunch sometimes she plays with her friend or reads,then she has lunch.She watches no T.V on Saturday.She puts her rabbit to bed,cleans her teeth,then she reads till eight thirty when she goes to bed.
